Package: joint2phase
Title: Joint Modeling of Ordinal and Continuous Outcomes in Two-Phase Designs
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("Yunbi", "Nam", , "yunbinam@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides functions for fitting joint models to ordinal and 
  continuous outcomes specifically designed for two-phase outcome-dependent sampling (ODS). 
  The package implements two-step and simultaneous estimation procedures, including
  Sieve Maximum Likelihood Estimation (SMLE) for ordinal probit models and
  EM algorithms for conditional and joint modeling. These methods account for 
  biased sampling and latent error correlations to provide valid inference for marginal effects.
